We (Carl Nicolai and I) decided to release NDC5's source code to the Net. 
It can be found at ripem.msu.edu in ~ftp/pub/crypto/other/ndc5src.zip, and
on cyberspace.com in ~ftp/pub/ndc5/ndc5src.zip.  ripem.msu.edu is export
controlled (i.e. Mark will only give you an account if you're a sworn U.S.
national, living in the U.S.A.).

As it stands, NDC5 is not a great piece of software.  It is an interesting
demonstration model of a unique crypto algorithm.  Hopefully someone finds
it fun to experiment with.
